Note: ============================================================================
Note: Identifier and Keyword Lexing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Scans an identifier starting at the current cursor (first char must
already have passed is_identifier_start). Consumes as long as
is_identifier_part returns 1 (letter, digit, or underscore). The
resulting lexeme is run through match_dart_keyword before token
construction so reserved words get the keyword tag rather than
TOKEN_IDENTIFIER.
@End Reasoning

Process called "lex_identifier" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Lex identifier or keyword

    Let source be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lexer, 0
    Let start_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lexer, 8
    Let line be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lexer, 16
    Let column be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with lexer, 24

    While 1 is equal to 1:
