Note: ============================================================================
Note: Main Tokenization
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The main lexing entry point: skip whitespace and comments (including
Dart's nested /* */ form), then peek the next character to route to the
appropriate sub-lexer. Returns one token per call, or a TOKEN_EOF when
the cursor has reached the precomputed source length. All multi-char
operators (==, !=, <=, >=, &&, ||, =>, ??, ?., ...) are recognised via
peek-and-consume rather than a separate maximal-munch table because the
operator set is small.
@End Reasoning

Process called "next_token" takes lexer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get next token from source

    @Reasoning:
    Main tokenization loop that handles:
    - Whitespace and comment skipping
    - Keywords and identifiers
    - Numbers (int, double, hex, scientific)
    - Strings (single/double/triple quote, raw, interpolation)
    - Operators (arithmetic, logical, bitwise, assignment, null-aware)
    - Punctuation
    - EOF
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Skip whitespace and comments
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        proc skip_whitespace with lexer

        Let ch be proc current_char with lexer

        If ch is equal to 47:
            Let next_ch be proc peek_char with lexer, 1

            If next_ch is equal to 47:
                proc skip_line_comment with lexer

